{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Locate to marker ID via OSC\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Written by Ben Smith - July 2021\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The default option for moving the Reaper's playhead to a particular marker only works with the order of markers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This script allows you to specify a marker number (i.e. marker ID) to navigate to.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Trigger this script via OSC. You will need to set a custom trigger.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Select a custom command to trigger the action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Go into the actions list, select the action, and next to the "shortcuts" list, click "add".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Send the command (this will ignore any value attached).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab As an argument in your OSC command, include the marker ID you wish to locate to divided by 1000.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab E.g. for marker 21, send {\f1 /reaper/marker_cue 0.021}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This is because the reaper.get_action_context() command will only return the value of an OSC message if it is between 0 and 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The resolution of the interpreted value is 16383.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This script is intended to be used in conjuction with Figure 53's {\i QLab} software, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/bsmith96/Qlab-Scripts/blob/master/Tech%20Rehearsals/Locate%20to%20Reaper%20Marker.applescript"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
this script
}}}
 within Qlab.\sa180\par}
}

