{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Set track inputs 1-to-1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Written by Ben Smith - July 2021\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Sets the track input channel sequentially, allowing you to set up projects with high track counts and quickly route the appropriate inputs to them.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab This is ideal for recording live performances, such as concerts or theatre.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab All tracks are presumed mono.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab To use stereo tracks, append the names with "--2".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Stereo tracks MUST start on odd input.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If your stereo tracks start with an even input (i.e. even/odd pair) the script will create {\i split stereo} tracks, a mono left and a mono right.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 User customisation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab stereoSuffix: "--2"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Allows you to customise the naming convention for indicating stereo tracks to the script.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab stereoSplitSuffix: [".L", ".R"]\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Customise how stereo tracks which are split to mono are renamed. e.g. "Left", ".L"\sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Metapackage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set track inputs 1-to-1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Sets every track input to the track number\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set track inputs 1-to-1 for selected tracks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Only affects selected tracks\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set track inputs 1-to-1 ignoring folders\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Assumes folders are used simply for structure, and does not include these.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab If track 1 is a folder and track 2 is not, track 2 will use input 1.\sa180\sa180\par}
}

