{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Explode multichannel audio files non-destructively\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Written by Ben Smith - August 2021\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Info\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Quickly explode multichannel audio files into individual tracks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Allows you to either explode a single track into x tracks, or to leave the selected track in place as a folder and place the individual stems inside it.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Explodes the selected multichannel audio file onto\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A new set of tracks below the current one, muting the original file.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab The existing tracks below the current one, muting the original file (e.g. if you have multiple recordings with the same channels).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab A new set of tracks in a folder of the current one, muting the original file.\sa180\sa180\par}
}

